          <div class="bio">
            <div class="name-and-company">Kim Bennett Horvath: <a href="http://www.solasalonstudios.com" target="_blank">Sola Salon Studios</a></div>
            <div class="text">
              Kim Bennett Horvath's passion as a hairdresser has taken her on a journey through the beauty industry for 25 years. As a licensed cosmetologist since the age of 18, she has continued to catapult her career and her business from her humble small town beginnings, and is dedicated to inspiring others in the beauty industry.
              <br><br>
              As a Senior National Educator for Paul Mitchell for the past 23 years she was one of the first Artistic Color Coordinators chosen to help launch Paul Mitchell's first color line, as well as being a Task Force Leader where she trained and coached regional Paul Mitchell National Educators. She received the Paul Mitchell Focus Award in 2012, and continues to educate and help salons grow their business.
              <br><br>
              While working in all aspects of traditional salons, Kim made the decision of salon ownership after meeting Sola's co-founders, Matt and Stratton, at a coffee shop in Denver, Colorado. Kim quickly became the first Sola Professional in early 2004! Throughout her 11+ years at Sola, Kim has supported and represented Sola Salon Studios in myriad ways and in early 2014 became Sola's Director of Education. Within this role, Kim uses her expertise to share the Sola Salon Studios culture to connect and build relationships throughout the Professional Beauty Industry.
              <br><br>
              Her passion and success as a Sola Professional has spread like wildfire being asked to speak with industry leaders on better business practices and has been featured in many publications including Modern Salon, Behind the Chair, and Milady Pro. She was also recently recognized as a Role Model by American Salon. Kim is dedicated to creating education opportunities for Sola Professionals to inspire them to become successful business owners while also enjoying their best artistic self.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bio">
            <div class="name-and-company">Nina Kovner: <a href="http://passionsquared.net/" target="_blank">PassionSquared</a></div>
            <div class="text">
              From the shampoo room to the boardroom, Nina L. Kovner took the world of pro beauty by storm with her thoughtful attention to detail and never-ending tenacity. After 26 years of conquering obstacles in an ever-changing business landscape and helping to build one of the most recognized professional hair care brands in the world, she respectfully walked away from a career at the top to help small business owners and artists discover and live their purpose with passion and empower their businesses. Now, as Chief Awesomeness Empowerer at Passion Squared, she wakes up every morning saying to herself… &quot;How I am going to help people create their own kind of awesome today?&quot;
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bio">
            <div class="name-and-company">Kelly Ehlers: <a href="http://www.wella.com/professional/en-US/home" target="_blank">Wella</a></div>
            <div class="text">
              Kelly Ehlers is the Founder and CEO of Ideas That Evoke, a Midwest-based social media agency that was recently named one of the &quot;Best Entrepreneurial Companies in America&quot; by Entrepreneur Magazine.
              <br><br>
              Additionally, Kelly was named the Enterprising Woman of the Year in 2015 by Enterprising Women Magazine, and was a semi-finalist for Entrepreneur Magazine's &quot;2014 Emerging Entrepreneur of the Year.&quot;
              <br><br>
              Kelly's rapidly growing agency works with global and domestic salon and spa professional brands, from Wella Professionals, Red Door Spa, Elizabeth Arden and Andis Professional - to a variety of lifestyle and luxury brands, including multiple Procter and Gamble brands. The foundation of the agency is built on solving business challenges for brands, through social innovation – and has been doing so since 2009.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bio">
            <div class="name-and-company">Jennie Wolff: <a href="https://www.solasalonstudios.com" target="_blank">Sola Salon Studios</a></div>
            <div class="text">
              After graduating from Emory University with a degree in Creative Writing, Jennie ventured to Colorado to break into Denver's entertainment scene, and was quickly hired by Kroenke Sports &amp; Entertainment. After 5 years of managing Kroenke's Special Events department, Jennie joined Motive, a boutique creative marketing agency. While at Motive, she worked on experiential campaigns and digital projects for top brands such as Mars Chocolate, Van's Natural Foods and Cartoon Network.
              In 2013, Matt and Stratton (Sola's co-founders) convinced Jennie to turn her talents toward the salon industry. As Sola's Vice President of Marketing and Education, Jennie manages the Sola marketing efforts top-to-bottom, including Sola's social media strategy, the Sola blog, Sola's website, all of Sola's traditional and nontraditional marketing campaigns, innovative stylist programs and more recently, the Sola Pro app and The Sola Sessions.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bio">
            <div class="name-and-company">Luis Alvarez: <a href="http://www.aquage.com/" target="_blank">Aquage</a></div>
            <div class="text">
              Join Aquage Co-founder, VP of Creative and award-winning designer, Luis Alvarez, at this exciting event.
              <br><br>
              Luis was knighted into the L'Ordre de la Chevalerie, one of the highest honors given by Intercoiffure, he was voted one of Modern Salon's 50 Most Influential Hairdressers and awarded the prestigious LEO Award from
              Pivot Point International.
              <br><br>
              His internationally renowned expertise in product development, image making and education is born out of his unique history spanning over 30 years in the fashion and beauty industry. First, he has been the creative driving force behind the formulation of all Aquage and Biomega products. Second, after working for many years as a freelance hairdresser with top fashion photographers, magazine editors and models, he became a photographer himself and created the powerful visual imagery Aquage is known for throughout the salon industry. Third, Luis elevates education to the highest level, leading the Aquage team of artists and top educators on the stage, at shows, educational events and at Aquage Masterclass academies across the country.
              <br><br>
              To Luis, knowledge is an energy source we can all tap into to inspire creative growth. As a leader and educator, he believes that the secret to elevating our craft lies in our ability to share knowledge. His engaging style, refreshing attitude and a penchant for creating truly beautiful and exciting styles, makes Luis one of the most sought-after talents in the beauty industry. His passion and creative vision bring innovation, education and inspiration to the professional salon industry.
              <br><br>
              For more information contact Wanda Alvarez at <a href="mailto:wanda@aquage.com">wanda@aquage.com</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bio">
            <div class="name-and-company">Nicole Gary: <a href="http://www.aquage.com/" target="_blank">Aquage</a></div>
            <div class="text">
              Aquage Styles Director, Nicole Gary, was a 2015 NAHA Finalist in the Newcomer Stylist of the Year and Avant Garde categories and was a 2014 NAHA Student Hairstylist of the Year award winner. Nicole's impressive work is featured in the Aquage ARIA DVD collection, which showcases modern, fashion-relevant, yet timeless special occasion styles crafted with fast, innovative, techniques.
              <br><br>
              Nicole also produces Aquage trade shows and educational events while managing to remain at the top of her game creatively. She also trains new Aquage educators when they join the team, teaches classes in our top salons and is an empowering learning leader at the Aquage Masterclass Academies.
              <br><br>
              Nicole possesses the unique ability to create inspired, original hair designs that translate easily to the salon. Her creative vision is expressed beautifully in the undone-elegance of her styles. Her charismatic personality and personal integrity assures you a highly successful Aquage learning experience.
              <br><br>
              For more information contact Wanda Alvarez at <a href="mailto:wanda@aquage.com">wanda@aquage.com</a>
