            <div class="text">
              Aquage Master Artist, Nogodar Martinez, is an international editorial hairdresser and one of the creative artists showcased in the Aquage EN POINTE, ARIA and MUSE Collections. Nogo invents and designs his innovative styles featuring simple, quick techniques that can be used to create stunning shapes, iconic forms, intricate textures, overlays and patterns that translate easily to the salon. Nogo's multi-cultural vibe and technical expertise make his one-of-a-kind hairstyles truly memorable. His charismatic personality and genuine passion for the art of hairdressing make Nogo an exciting talent and a valuable asset to the Aquage team.
              <br><br>
              You do not want to miss an educational event with Aquage Master Artist Nogodar Martinez.
              <br><br>
              For more information contact Wanda Alvarez at <a href="mailto:wanda@aquage.com">wanda@aquage.com</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bio">
            <div class="name-and-company">DJ Muldoon: <a href="http://www.thefactoryhair.com/" target="_blank">theFactory</a></div>
            <div class="text">
              DJ joined Vidal Sassoon as a cosmetology student in 1994. Little did he know what an impact this would have on his journey. There he joined the ranks of what is now known as a legendary group of haircutting, coloring and styling educators and industry leaders.
              <br><br>
              After a few short years DJ had become one of Vidal Sassoon's most sought after educators, ‘teacher of the year' in his first year of teaching, and established himself as a member of the Creative Team under the guidance of Tim Hartley. Here he developed his skill as an educator working side by side with his mentors and peers Traci Sakosits, Gerard Scarpaci, Wayne Woodruff, Stephen Moody, Julian Perlingiero, Lucie Doughty amongst many others who helped lay the foundation of what would become the Vidal Sassoon ABC system.
              <br><br>
              By 2002 DJ transitioned onto the next phase of his career by joining the Paul Mitchell organization to create Paul Mitchell the School's haircutting system and curriculum. While at Paul Mitchell he became a global platform artist sharing his knowledge and skill to a worldwide audience. This gave DJ the ability in the mid 2000's to start creating on other levels such as video production and ‘step by step' education, earning DJ the much coveted Hairbrained Video Award in 2014.
              <br><br>
              In 2011 DJ started theFactory, an independent creative production space, academy and salon based in San Diego, which gives DJ the ability to educate on many different levels such as hands-on education and web based education.
              <br><br>
              DJ is one the worlds most sought after teachers in the industry because of his no fluff approach and his ability to breakdown the what, why, how, and when in haircutting. He believes that ‘Knowledge Destroys Fear' and he is proud to represent the hairdresser as an independent artist.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bio">
            <div class="name-and-company">Justin Isaac: <a href="http://www.redken.com/international/" target="_blank">Redken</a></div>
            <div class="text">
              Color is the fire that lit the passion and it is this fire that Justin Isaac brings to inspire artists around the world.
              <br><br>
              Justin Isaac is known throughout the industry as the most creative colorist where remixing concepts and simplifying advanced ideas – just a couple of his many talents. No matter the venue or the language, he breaks it down for all to feel the vibe and be part of it.
              <br><br>
              Justin Isaac has traveled the globe sharing the flavor of Redken NYC. His travels include South Africa, Thailand, Chile, Mexico, Japan, Malaysia, Taiwan, Canada, Singapore and Germany. It is through these travels that he has been able to re-energize his spirit and share the vibe these many cultures have to offer as inspiration in the US. In 2008, Justin Isaac will be sharing this inspiration in Art 4 Color and Art 4 Life – a two-day specialty class at the Redken Exchange revolving around art, color and self-reflection with one of the days held in Central Park.
              <br><br>
              Justin Isaac has been a Redken Artist since 1998, a facilitator at the Redken Exchange since 2000 and a featured Redken Symposium artist. His work has also been part of Redken Creates Volume 1.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bio">
            <div class="name-and-company">Carmody Homan: <a href="http://www.redken.com/international/" target="_blank">Redken</a></div>
            <div class="text">
              "fashion… it's all I know…it's how I was raised…"
              <br><br>
              Growing up in New Zealand, it wasn't your typical kiwi setting, models lined our living room walls like magazine covers waiting for their turn to be fitted for my dad's upcoming Fashion Shows. Most kids would remember seeing their dad with a scarf around their neck…a tape measure is what I remember my dad wore. It all started with my grandmother who too, designed and made her own clothes. Needless to say my dad would follow in her footsteps. I was at the age of 15 styling the model's hair for my dad's fashion shows. I never stopped, I never looked back. Hair became my needle and thread as fashion remained my point of view, it's just in my blood.
              <br><br>
              INTERNATIONAL ARTISTIC DIRECTOR TONI &amp; GUY UK, TO REDKEN 5TH AVE, FACE OF REDKEN STYLE CONNECTION LINE, TO EDITORIAL MAGAZINES, SESSION STYLING, FASHION CONSULTING FOR MAJOR BRANDS, ULTA CREATIVE CONSULTANT.
            </div>
